ntrepreneursDemonstrate makerspace technology and recording studio equipment to staff, empowering and supporting staff in the delivery of related services.In consultation with the IT department, maintain relevant equipment and softwareActively seek out and recommend new trends in maker and creator technology, both digital and analogStay current with emerging technologiesManage and maintain makerspace equipment, ensuring all equipment and accessories are present and in good working conditionMaintain a supply inventory and advise Supervisor when restocking is requiredThe Ideal CandidateWe are seeking a candidate with maker knowledge normally acquired through a post-secondary degree/diploma in art, design or technology, or a closely related field. Our ideal candidate has two years of public experience as well as two years in a customer-focused setting. We are seeking people with excellent communication and customer service skills as well as superior interpersonal skills including the ability to work effectively in a team environment and foster effective working relationships.This position offers a salary range of $70,059.31 - $84,576.06 plus a competitive benefit package.Notwithstanding the above, candidates who do not fulfill all of our requirements may be considered in a Development Status capacity. Satisfactory passing of a vulnerable sector check, and proof of qualifications will be required of any successful candidate(s) for this position.The Town is an equal opportunity employer that is committed to an inclusive and barrier-free workplace. If your application requires accommodation, please contact Human Resources at (905) 584-2272 Ext. 4738.How To ApplyTo learn more about employment with the Town of Caledon and to apply for this exciting and challenging opportunity, visit: www.caledon.ca/careersIf needed and upon request, this document can be made available in an alternative format. Compensation $70,059.31 - $84,576.06 Closes: 5 May, 2024 Caledon Public Library C